3.Event Driven Execution.
Workflow:
1.Sequential.
2.Event Driven.
Langchain is not built for event driven execution.
Langgraph is event driven.

4.Fault tolerance.
Important in long-running work flow.
Faults:
1.Small fault.
2.Big fault.
In langchain, if the system get broken it cannot recover and start again from that point..it will have to start from the beginning.
whereas, in langgraph..we have retry logic which can take care of small level fault.
for big fault..we have recovery in langgraph.

